# Patch 0031 — Settings consolidation: Appearance & Themes + Customization
# panes in about:preferences (ROADMAP Phase 3 UX; ADR 0009/0021 pane pattern).
#
# WHAT: two Kavacha Settings panes, added with Zen's own four-file pane recipe
# (the same one patch 0021's Privacy Center uses).
#   - paneKavachaAppearance ("Appearance & Themes"): a theme picker over
#     KavachaThemeEngine.listThemes()/resolveTheme()/setActiveTheme() (patch
#     0023), an accent-color control bound to the user-owned zen.theme.accent-color
#     pref with a "Use system accent" reset, a new-tab dashboard/floating-search
#     toggle over zen.urlbar.replace-newtab, and a "Customize visually in the
#     Studio →" button to about:studio.
#   - paneKavachaCustomization ("Customization"): layout controls (tab style,
#     sidebar position, density, toolbar visibility) over
#     KavachaLayoutEngine.getLayout()/setLayout() (patch 0022, watching the
#     kavacha.layout.revision doorbell), a "Custom CSS safe mode" checkbox over
#     KavachaUserCSS (patch 0025), and links out to about:studio (Advanced),
#     about:marketplace (patch 0028) and about:plugins (patch 0029).
#
# WHY: "all the options and theme stuff should be in that [settings menu]".
# about:preferences becomes the one settings home — the patch-0030 top-right
# menu's "Settings" row lands here. These panes are deliberately THIN views over
# the already-shipped engines (they only read/write the engines' public APIs and
# their prefs, and apply live to every window); the rich visual surfaces stay in
# the about: pages, one click away. No engine logic is duplicated.
#
# WHY A PATCH: Zen's Settings pane registration is spread across meta-patch files
# (preferences-xhtml.patch / preferences-js.patch / jar-mn.patch) that only a
# patch can extend; an overlay/pref cannot register a preferences pane. Follows
# ADR 0021's recipe exactly — the register_module template-inline guard already
# matches categoryName.startsWith("paneKavacha"), so both paneKavacha* ids render.
#
# NOT BUILD-VERIFIED (no Firefox tree built in this environment). The two
# controllers pass `node --check`; the meta-patch edits keep their inner unified
# diffs count-consistent; the outer diff applies cleanly on top of 0030 with
# `git apply --check`. Applies on top of 0030.
#
# Touches: locales/en-US/browser/browser/preferences/zen-preferences.ftl;
# src/browser/components/preferences/{jar-mn,preferences-js,preferences-xhtml}.patch;
# src/browser/components/preferences/kavacha-appearance.js (new);
# src/browser/components/preferences/kavacha-customization.js (new);
# src/browser/components/preferences/kavachaAppearance.inc.xhtml (new);
# src/browser/components/preferences/kavachaCustomization.inc.xhtml (new);
# src/browser/themes/shared/preferences/zen-preferences.css.
